sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant B as Browser (React)
    participant W as Web (Express)
    participant DB as Postgres
    participant R as Redis (queue + pub/sub)
    participant WK as Worker

    Note over B: EventSource already open on GET /messages/stream<br/>(mounted once when the app loads)

    B->>B: setMessages #1 — optimistic user echo<br/>id = crypto.randomUUID()  (FE list key, NEVER sent)
    B->>W: POST /messages { text }
    W->>DB: addMessage(userMessage)<br/>id = crypto.randomUUID()  (DB user-row id — different, fine)
    Note over W: const assistantId = crypto.randomUUID()<br/>*** the claim ticket is printed ***
    W-->>B: 202 { id: assistantId }
    Note over B: setMessages #2 — empty assistant bubble<br/>stamped { id: assistantId, streaming: true }<br/>setIsTyping(false) — typing-dots bridge handed off
    W->>R: enqueueReply(assistantId) → add("reply", { id })

    R->>WK: job.data = { id: assistantId }
    WK->>DB: getMessages() → history
    Note over WK: graph.stream(...) — LangGraph agent generates the reply

    loop every token chunk
        WK->>R: emitToken(assistantId, chunk)<br/>publish { type:"token", id, chunk }
        R->>W: SSE subscriber receives (sub.on "message")
        W-->>B: event: token  data { id: assistantId, chunk }
        B->>B: msg.id === assistantId ? append chunk : leave
    end

    WK->>DB: addMessage({ id: assistantId, text: full })
    WK->>R: emitDone(assistantId)  publish { type:"done", id }
    R->>W: SSE subscriber receives
    W-->>B: event: done  data { id: assistantId }
    B->>B: msg.id === assistantId ? streaming: false : leave

    Note over B,WK: One ticket (assistantId) rides every arrow after the 202.<br/>The two other ids never leave their box.
